abstract: But he plays one on TV. That’s a problem.
snippet: But he plays one on TV. That’s a problem.
lead_paragraph: Republicans have a long, disreputable history of conflating any attempt to improve American lives with the evils of “socialism.” When Medicare was first proposed, Ronald Reagan called it “socialized medicine,” and he declared that it would destroy our freedom. These days, if you call for something like universal child care, conservatives accuse you of wanting to turn America into the Soviet Union.

abstract: The billionaire drew condemnation for his newly surfaced comments on redlining, in which banks discriminated against people of color seeking to borrow money to afford homes.
snippet: The billionaire drew condemnation for his newly surfaced comments on redlining, in which banks discriminated against people of color seeking to borrow money to afford homes.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg, the Democratic presidential candidate and former mayor of New York City, drew criticism on Thursday over newly surfaced comments from the height of the 2008 financial crisis in which he said that the end of redlining, a discriminatory housing practice, had helped contribute to the economic collapse.

abstract: President Trump and the Democratic presidential hopeful Michael R. Bloomberg exchanged sharp words on Twitter.
snippet: President Trump and the Democratic presidential hopeful Michael R. Bloomberg exchanged sharp words on Twitter.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump and Michael R. Bloomberg, the former mayor of New York City, have been slinging insults at each other for weeks, but their Twitter war reached a new level on Thursday.

headline_main: ‘Mass of Dead Energy’ vs. ‘Barking Clown’: Trump and Bloomberg Swap Insults

abstract: A business school professor who studied the benefits of diversity in the workplace and spoke to companies about it.
snippet: A business school professor who studied the benefits of diversity in the workplace and spoke to companies about it.
lead_paragraph: Growing up in a black neighborhood of Chicago, Katherine W. Phillips was chosen in third grade to attend a nearly all-white magnet school. “I was introduced at a young age to diversity, to difference, to ignorance,” she later recalled.

abstract: President Trump had a busy morning on Twitter and the radio, in a tirade that rivaled his most grievance-filled moments since becoming president.
snippet: President Trump had a busy morning on Twitter and the radio, in a tirade that rivaled his most grievance-filled moments since becoming president.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump made a number of staff moves on Thursday to ensure he will be surrounded by a cadre of loyalists at the White House even as he raged against an ever-growing cast of perceived enemies that included his former chief of staff, an impeachment witness, a juror he accused of bias and a Democratic rival.

abstract: The candidates take a breath, and a top Iowa Democrat resigns. This is your morning tip sheet.

lead_paragraph: Late at night, journalists gathered at Klobuchar’s “Amy for America” primary night party in Concord, N.H., after her third-place finish in the state.

headline_main: Coronavirus, Justice Department, Democrats: Your Thursday Briefing

abstract: Joe Biden is looking ahead to South Carolina to resurrect his candidacy. There are signs that it may be a bigger challenge after defeats in Iowa and New Hampshire.
snippet: Joe Biden is looking ahead to South Carolina to resurrect his candidacy. There are signs that it may be a bigger challenge after defeats in Iowa and New Hampshire.
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — Even before the final results from New Hampshire showed Joseph R. Biden Jr. finishing a distant fifth there, the former vice president had flown to South Carolina on Tuesday night for a gathering of enthusiastic supporters. A gospel choir sang about salvation, a fitting choice for a candidate who is counting on this state’s large black electorate to save his third try for the White House.
